history.text: Hi.
Hello.  Would you be interested in seeing a superhero action film directed by Zack Snyder?  Although the critical responses were lacking, it has an ensemble cast.
Yes I always watch those.
Although Batman and Superman are both great characters, it is great to have Wonder Woman in this film.
Yeah Wonder Woman is awesome!
Would you be interested in seeing Batman vs. Superman?
Sure, in fact I did!  It was good and I enjoyed it.
Did you know that the critical responses were mixed?
I didn't remember about that.
Do you tend to not look at reviews about superhero films?
Basically I just look at the trailer, and then I go.
If possible, I would like to discuss some key scenes with you.  Specifically, how Superman has become a controversial figure.
Yes, please do.
Did you know that Batman sees him as a threat to humanity?
I think I remember that.
I liked this because it puts the two characters at odds, which reinforces the title.
Yes it makes it more intense.
It's really sad when Luthor kidnaps Lois and Martha Kent, right?
Yes that's sad.
How did you feel about Superman saying "Save Martha" to Batman?
I think it helped them to get on the same side.
I think it was great that Batman saved Superman and Martha
Yes it was very helpful.
Superman's death was also very sad.  Do you agree with Luthor that his death has mad the world vulnerable to powerful alien threats?
Yes if Superman dies than some alien presence that is equal to him would be more difficult to stop.
Due to the complex emotional nature of the film's plot, what do you think about the 27% Rotten Tomato's score?

I just don't care about that, it had plenty of grit in its bones without the critics'
 approval.
I really liked the final scene where the dirt atop Clark's coffin levitates.  Did you?

uid2response.feedback: The user talked fine about the critics' response.
